definitions.definition: A usually translucent and somewhat elastic , dense , nonvascular connective tissue found in various forms in the larynx and respiratory tract , in structures such as the external ear , and in the articulating surfaces of joints . It composes most of the skeleton of vertebrate embryos , being replaced by bone during ossification in the higher vertebrates.
A particular structure made of cartilage.
